  abstract          = {The proceedings contain 37 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Robotics Research. The topics include: 6N-DoF Pose Tracking for Tensegrity Robots; scale-Invariant Fast Functional Registration; towards Mapping of Underwater Structures by a Team of Autonomous Underwater Vehicles; contact-Implicit Planning and Control for Non-prehensile Manipulation Using State-Triggered Constraints; mechanical Search on Shelves with Efficient Stacking and Destacking of Objects; multi-object Grasping in the Plane; parameter Estimation for Deformable Objects in Robotic Manipulation Tasks; place-and-Pick-Based Re-grasping Using Unstable Placement; safe, Occlusion-Aware Manipulation for Online Object Reconstruction in Confined Spaces; cooperation of Assistive Robots to Improve Productivity in the Nursing Care Field; learning Agile, Vision-Based Drone Flight: From Simulation to Reality; Adaptive Radiation Survey Using an Autonomous Robot Executing LiDAR Scans in the Large Hadron Collider; reference-Free Learning Bipedal Motor Skills via Assistive Force Curricula; ball-and-Socket Joint Pose Estimation Using Magnetic Field; bulletArm: An Open-Source Robotic Manipulation Benchmark and Learning Framework; Optimization-Based Online Flow Fields Estimation for AUVs Navigation; flying Hydraulically Amplified Electrostatic Gripper System for Aerial Object Manipulation; hybrid Quadratic Programming - Pullback Bundle Dynamical Systems Control; riemannian Geometry as a Unifying Theory for Robot Motion Learning and Control; ensured Continuous Surveillance Despite Sensor Transition Using Control Barrier Functions; nonlinear Stochastic Trajectory Optimization for Centroidal Momentum Motion Generation of Legged Robots; Continual SLAM: Beyond Lifelong Simultaneous Localization and Mapping Through Continual Learning; reactive Anticipatory Robot Skills with Memory; ROSE: Robust State Estimation via Online Covariance Adaption; what Can Algebraic Topology and Differential G